  , issueCommentBody =
      "In reql-admin you can pass a configuration directly to `table_create()`, or alternatively create tables by writing a document into the new `rethinkdb.table_config` pseudo table.\r\n\r\nYou could simply create a table `\"db_default_table_configs\"` yourself where you store the defaults for your different DBs.\r\nThen you could run:\r\n```\r\nr.db(rethinkdb).table('table_config').insert(r.table('db_default_table_configs').get(dbName).merge({name: tableName}) )\r\n```\r\nto create a table called `tableName` with all defaults applied.\r\n\r\nI think that will solve this use case and also #3334?"
